description: A future Dark Age. After a catastrophic past, humanity is facing an uncertain future. A terrible disease – Ossidancy – is scourging the oil metropolis called Civilian, that survived for decades trading the black gold for the only known medicine: the healthy blood of Lith’s citizen… Now their alliance has failed, and for the plagued population there’s no other way but the exile. That’s the path taken by Joe, who lives in the desert with his friend Arco, resigned to wait for an unavoidable ending. But their waiting will be disrupted by a young woman, Alba, and the clouds of war that are building up on the horizon!
name: Oxid Age

description: While the world plunges into the hell of the Second World War, two men – Private Tom Hamilton and Airman Jonas D’Arcy – fight their own little private war. A war of boxers, of fists and sweat, fueled by a mutual hate as inexorable as seemingly devoid of a reason… The puzzling struggle told in a classic of universal literature – Joseph Conrad’s “The Duellists” – is now born again among the waste of the biggest tragedy of the XX century!
name: I Combattenti

description: Warren Ellis trade paperback collects the limited series Down issues #1-4, as well as Tales of the Witchblade issues #3-#4. Written by Warren Ellis (Transmetropolitan, The Authority), here you can follow the adventures of Detective Deanna Ransom as she goes deep undercover to bring back a cop gone bad, as well as a story of the Witchblade from the not so distant future.

Get previews of 2015's hottest horror stories including:

Harrow County, Colder: Toss the Bones, The Steam Man, Dead Vengeance, B.P.R.D. Hell on Earth, Joe Golem, Hellboy and the B.P.R.D., and Rat God!

Eight different stories and over 80 pages of horror for FREE!

Contents

Dragon Ball Super - Chapter 5: Birusu to Shanpa

Three masked robbers storm at night, weapons in hand, into a big insane asylum. Nobody knows who they are and what they’re looking for. One thing is for sure, though: they have a less-than-tight plan. The situation turns bad fast, blood begins to be shed and the automatic security system blocks every way out. It’s the beginning of a slow and tense psychological agony, a frenzied and claustrophobic escalation that will peak in dramatic and unpredictable end...
name: La Gabbia

description: World War I, the fire and mud inferno of the trenches on the French front. A patrol of British soldiers is sent on a risky reconnaissance mission: they’ll have to explore the “Castle”, a German fortification where there hasn’t been any sign of life since a few days… Inside it, they’ll only find a pile of dead bodies: the enemies were exterminated by their own poison gas… Beside the mangled corpses, though, something else is waiting for them in that ghostly place, something concealed in the shadow and ready to strike… and kill!
name: L'Ultima Trincea

description: Stuck in the Gutters brings you another 50+ page issue that's part comics anthology and part comics journalism. Contributors to this issue include Ryan K Lindsay, Dan Hill, Kelly Williams, Jeremy Holt, Ricardo Mo, Jordan Kroeger, Caroline Johnson and Graham Johnson, and many more!
After being dosed with a new strain of Scarecrow's fear gas, Bane is unleashed by the Arkham Knight, armed with the knowledge of Batman's secret identity!
